Singer Naira Marley has reacted to the arrest of his musical acts Oniyide Azeez (Zinoleesky) and Mohbad (Ilerioluwa Oladimeji) by operatives of The National Drug Law Enforcement Agency (NDLEA). The Marlian records signees were arrested after a midnight raid on their residence in the Lekki area of Lagos. In a viral Instagram video, the agents were seen hitting the artists and forcing them into a waiting bus.   Ex-BBNaija’s Lucy lambasts those doubting her age     How I almost missed my convocation, by Obi Cubana     NDLEA picks up Marlian music acts as Naira Marley reacts   Some ladies with the artistes at the time of the arrest were heard screaming and condemning the violence meted out on the music stars. Following the incident, the Marlian Records boss via his Insta story expressed indignation over his signee’s arrest by the NDLEA operatives. The “Soapy” singer said: “I’m so fucking angry RN walahi.”